# Component Tiers

Every section in this starter has two tiers. Always respect which tier you're working in.

## Tier 1 — `Brief*` (`components/briefs/`)

- Single-page / landing-page sites
- Compact, no forms, no heavy interactions
- Uses the **same dict** as its Tier 2 counterpart
- Renders shared sub-components from `components/sections/<section>/`

## Tier 2+ — `*Section` (`components/sections/<section>/`)

- Multi-page sites or dedicated section pages
- Full-featured: forms, tabs, filters, etc.
- Uses the same shared sub-components as the Tier 1 Brief
- Can be composed on the home page alongside briefs (e.g. `ContactSection` + `BriefContact`, `TestimonialsSection` + `BriefTestimonials` on HomePage)

## Shared sub-components (`components/sections/<section>/`)

- Reusable pieces used by **both** tiers
- Must never depend on which tier is rendering them

**Concrete example — Contact:**

```
components/sections/contact/
  contact-info.tsx     ← shared: email/phone/address with icons, pulls from shared.ts
  contact-form.tsx     ← shared: the actual form (Tier 2+ only via ContactSection)
  contact-section.tsx  ← Tier 2+: two-col, ContactInfo left + ContactForm right

components/briefs/
  BriefContact.tsx     ← Tier 1: SectionHeading + ContactInfo, no form, period
```

## Adding a new section

1. Create shared sub-component(s) in `components/sections/<section>/`
2. `components/briefs/Brief<Section>.tsx` — Tier 1, uses the sub-component(s), no form
3. `components/sections/<section>/<Section>Section.tsx` — Tier 2+, same sub-components + extras
4. Follow the dictionary-architecture rule for any new copy fields

## Rules

1. **Never add a form to a `Brief*` component.** Forms belong in `*Section` only.
2. **Never duplicate contact info, site name, or social links** — always pull from `content/shared.ts`.
3. **Shared sub-components have no tier awareness** — they receive props or pull from `shared`, never from a tier-specific context.
4. **Dict shape is shared** — both tiers use the same getter (e.g. `getContactDict`). Don't create separate dicts per tier.
